# jQuery Plugins

jQuery simplifies common javascript tasks:
1. Selecting and manipulating page elements
2. Sending and receiving data using AJAX
3. Adding engaging visual effects to a web page

example:
1. jCalculator - http://codepen.io/mariusbalaj/pen/bGqhI
2. jQuery Adaptive Model - http://www.thepetedesign.com/demos/adaptive-modal_demo.html
3. jQuery ListNav - http://ericsteinborn.com/jquery-listnav/
4. video background (VIDE) - http://vodkabears.github.io/vide/
5. lightbox - http://lokeshdhakar.com/projects/lightbox2/
6. jQuery UI - https://jqueryui.com/
7. Animsition - http://git.blivesta.com/animsition/

How to find the best plugins:
http://www.sitepoint.com/jquery-popular-plugins-list/
http://www.unheap.com/

1. Does something you need
2. Good documentation
3. Actively developed
4. Responsive friendly
5. Mobile friendly

Plugin includes:
1. JS File - required
2. CSS File
3. Images

Steps include in your project:
1. Attach Files
    1.1 Attach the CSS File (before your site's CSS file or files) (so you can overwrite the plugins using your CSS File)
    1.2 Attach the jQuery - use the jQuery CDN
    1.3 Attach the plugin JS File - after the jQuery CDN line
2. Structure your HTML (sometimes adding a classname or id)
3. Add our programming
    3.1 Add your own JS
    3.2 Select an element on the page using jQuery
    3.3 Call the plugin function




